withdraRequestStream.t.sol
├── when the request IS null
│   └── it should revert with the {NullRequest} error
└── when the request IS NOT null 
    ├── when the payment method IS transfer
    │   └── it should revert with the {OnlyForStreamPaymentMethods} error
    └── when the caller IS NOT transfer
        ├── when caller IS NOT the request recipient
        │   └── it should revert with the {OnlyStreamRecipient} error
        └── when caller IS request recipient
            ├── when `msg.value` IS NOT enough to cover the fee
            │   └── it should revert with the {InsufficientFee} error
            └── when `msg.value` IS enough to cover the fee
                ├── when the amount IS zero
                │   └── it should revert with the {ZeroWithdrawAmount} error
                └── when the amount IS NOT zero
                    ├── when the amount exceeds the withdrawable amount
                    │   └── it should revert with the {Overdraw} error
                    └── when the amount does not exceed the withdrawable amount
                        ├── given the payment method is linear stream
                        │   └── given the payment request status is Ongoing
                        │       └── it should allow the payment request recipient to withdraw maximum amount from the stream
                        └── given the payment method is tranched stream
                            └── given the payment request status is Ongoing
                                └── it should allow the payment request recipient to withdraw maximum amount from the stream